Functions¶

In [3]:
def project_point(p1, p2, t):
    x1, y1 = p1
    x2, y2 = p2  
    x0, y0 = t
    if (x1 == x2):
        return (x1, y0)
    m = (y1-y2)/(x1-x2)
    if m == 0:
        return (x0, y1)
    x = (y0-y1+x1*m+x0/m)/(m+1/m)  
    y = m * (x-x1) + y1
    return (x,y)


def distancepp(p1, p2):
    x1, y1 = p1
    x2, y2 = p2    
    return ((x1-x2)**2 + (y1-y2)**2)**0.5
    

def distance_line_point(p1, p2, t):
    pp = project_point(p1, p2, t)
    d = distancepp(t, pp)
    a = distancepp(p1, pp)
    b = distancepp(p2, pp)
    c = distancepp(p1,p2)    
    if ((a+b) <= c):
        return d
    else:
        return min(distancepp(p1, t),distancepp(p2, t)) 
    
def distance_edges_point(ed1, ed2, t):
    p1 = ed1.p
    p2 = ed2.p
    return distance_line_point(p1, p2, t)

def point_route_position(t, route_edges):
    L = len(route_edges)
    distances = []
    for k in range(L-1):
        d = distance_edges_point(route_edges[k], route_edges[k+1], t) 
        distances.append([d, route_edges[k].X])        
        
    return min(distances, key = lambda x: x[0])

Classes¶

In [4]:
class Edge():
    
    '''Edge of the path'''
    
    def __init__(self, lat, lon, k, X, route):
        self.lat = lat
        self.lon = lon
        self.k = k
        self.X = X
        self.route = route
        
    @property
    def p(self):
        return (self.lat, self.lon)
        
                
    def __repr__(self):
        return "{}\t#{}\tX={:.4f}".format(self.route, self.k, self.X)
    
a = Edge(0.1,0.1,2,1.21345, 'red')
print(a)
print(a.p)

    path_data = bs4.BeautifulSoup(routes_xml, 'lxml-xml')
    
routes = defaultdict(list)

for route in path_data.find_all('route'):
    route_tag = route.get("tag")
    print(route_tag)
    points = route.find_all("point")
    for point in points:
        lat = point.get('lat')
        lon = point.get('lon')
        routes[route_tag].append((lat, lon))
